        Creates a method for accepting a visitor. If methodBody is supplied, then the method is implemented; otherwise, it is abstract. [@Override] public [abstract] R accept(RootVisitor visitor) { [methodBody] }
        Parameters:
        node - The node of the class that this method is for
        rootName - The name of the root visitable class, used to generate the visitor's name
        methodBody - The method body, should execute one of the visitor argument's cases, or null if the method is abstract
        Returns:
        The corresponding method declaration
